1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:02,233
<i>- Hi, sissy!
- Oh!</i>

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:04,767
<i>I'm Sari!
Sir Martin's assistant.</i>

3
00:00:04,933 --> 00:00:06,600
<i> Assistant...</i>

4
00:00:06,767 --> 00:00:08,033
<i> This is Trixie. My sister.</i>

5
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:09,633
<i>- This is my sister, Cheska.
- Bro!</i>

6
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:10,967
<i>- Excuse me.
- Sorry.</i>

7
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:12,133
<i>- The earring...
- Jade.</i>

8
00:00:12,267 --> 00:00:14,367
<i>It's not Luna's.
It's Mom's.</i>

9
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:15,800
<i>Do you think Aunt Frida
had something to do</i>

10
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:17,433
<i> with their deaths?</i>

11
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:20,733
<i>I'm sure they got something
to do with what happened to me.</i>

12
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:21,767
<i> Mrs. Almazan,</i>

13
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:23,733
<i>where were you
when Michael Fernandez</i>

14
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:24,933
<i> and Frederico Almazan died?</i>

15
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:27,233
<i>You have no right to accuse
my mother.</i>

16
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:29,033
<i> We know about the earring.</i>

17
00:00:29,133 --> 00:00:32,267
<i>I'll only speak
in the presence of my lawyer.</i>

18
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:35,133
<i>I'm begging you.
Please, just leave.</i>

19
00:00:43,133 --> 00:00:48,300
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

20
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:49,333
[SIGHS]

21
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:51,767
Dear.

22
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:54,800
Your birthday is ruined
because of me.

23
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:56,833
I'm so sorry.

24
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:58,433
[JUSTIN]
No, of course not, Mom.

25
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,133
I'm glad to spend time
with you guys.

26
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:05,767
I've told you everything.

27
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,100
I'm not keeping anything
from you.

28
00:01:10,733 --> 00:01:12,800
You believe me, right?

29
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:13,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

30
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,300
Yes, Ma.

31
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:19,333
Ma, you don't have
to explain yourself again.

32
00:01:22,333 --> 00:01:23,500
[JUSTIN] Let's go, Mom.

33
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:25,833
I'll take you to your room.
Get some rest.

34
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:26,867
Okay.

35
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:31,267
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

36
00:01:31,367 --> 00:01:32,333
Luna.

37
00:01:34,667 --> 00:01:35,633
[EXHALES]

38
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,133
The question is,

39
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:42,367
how did the cops find out
about the earring?

40
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:52,200
[EXHALES]

41
00:01:53,733 --> 00:01:54,733
I'm leaving.

42
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:55,900
Keep an eye on Mom.

43
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:57,800
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

44
00:01:57,900 --> 00:02:04,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,200
[GLASS CLANKS]

46
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,767
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

47
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:35,200
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:03:27,867 --> 00:03:31,567
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:03:31,667 --> 00:03:32,600
Alright.

50
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:35,833
Slowly.

51
00:03:37,867 --> 00:03:39,433
Be sure to check the wiring.

52
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:40,667
There might be a short circuit.

53
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,400
I don't want any problems
on the day of the event.

54
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,900
Yes, sir.

55
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,433
Guys, be careful.

56
00:03:47,133 --> 00:03:48,467
Is this all set?

57
00:03:57,167 --> 00:03:58,267
What?

58
00:03:58,367 --> 00:03:59,800
Did Sir Henri message already?

59
00:03:59,967 --> 00:04:01,300
Not yet.

60
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,867
What happened there?

61
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,767
Have you talked to Jade?

62
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:07,167
Not yet.

63
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:09,467
But you're okay now?

64
00:04:09,633 --> 00:04:10,633
Yes.

65
00:04:10,733 --> 00:04:12,300
And you're right.

66
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,467
This is justice for Papa
and Uncle Fred.

67
00:04:14,633 --> 00:04:16,967
So this is the only
right thing to do.

68
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:19,333
They better get ready
for their lies.

69
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,367
It's getting obvious.

70
00:04:23,367 --> 00:04:24,500
Where are they?

71
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:27,200
They left early, right?

72
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:29,300
[SCOFFS]
It actually feels weird.

73
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:32,167
None of them are here.
No grumpy faces.

74
00:04:33,100 --> 00:04:36,333
It just feels so nice to
have the hotel to ourselves,

75
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:37,667
even if it's just
for one day.

76
00:04:37,767 --> 00:04:40,167
Feels good, right?
Just chill.

77
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:41,967
No annoying people.

78
00:04:42,067 --> 00:04:43,800
Yes, Lord!
This is the life, Lord.

79
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:45,033
[CHUCKLES]

80
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:50,833
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

81
00:04:50,933 --> 00:04:52,233
You want some
real chill?

82
00:05:02,367 --> 00:05:04,233
- Game?
- Come on.

83
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:05,733
Let's do it.

84
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:07,233
- You're the slow one, bro!
- I'm already ahead of you!

85
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,867
- Hurry up!
- Hey, Martin!

86
00:05:08,967 --> 00:05:09,900
- What?
- Come on already!

87
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:10,900
- What's up, bro?
- [LAUGHS]

88
00:05:11,067 --> 00:05:13,267
- You got nervous!
- You're blocking the way!

89
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,033
- Move it!
- You're all so slow!

90
00:05:15,133 --> 00:05:16,400
- Come on!
- Hey!

91
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:18,200
Faster, faster, faster!

92
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,700
What?
You guys are so slow!

93
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,867
Hey!

94
00:05:21,033 --> 00:05:22,367
Martin,
you're so slow!

95
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:24,200
All you do is complain!

96
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:25,433
What?

97
00:05:25,567 --> 00:05:27,433
You thought I was still
the same guy, didn't you?

98
00:05:27,567 --> 00:05:29,767
What? No way, bro!
You can't beat me now!

99
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:34,900
- What's up? Hey!
- Oh.

100
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,033
Here it comes!

101
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:38,933
- Goodbye!
- Hey!

102
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,800
[GRUNTS]

103
00:05:45,267 --> 00:05:52,067
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

104
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:04,967
Is Frida hiding something?
Is she protecting someone?

105
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,967
Michael and Federico have
had bad blood for a long time.

106
00:06:11,133 --> 00:06:13,600
No one knows why.

107
00:06:13,767 --> 00:06:16,267
Then suddenly,
they made up.

108
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:18,467
They even became partners
in Hotel 88.

109
00:06:19,933 --> 00:06:21,767
If they really
killed each other,

110
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:26,600
that means
they fought again.

111
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:29,767
But what could Frida possibly
have to do with all that?

112
00:06:29,867 --> 00:06:32,400
That's the question
we need to answer.

113
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,100
Or maybe...

114
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:36,467
she's protecting someone?

115
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:38,733
Or maybe she really
is involved in the mess.

116
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:44,033
If my suspicion
turns out to be true,

117
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:47,600
what would be
Mrs. Almazan's motive?

118
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:54,467
What could two men
possibly fight about...

119
00:06:54,633 --> 00:06:56,333
...that involves a woman?

120
00:06:56,500 --> 00:07:03,467
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

121
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:14,800
His hair was long.
About this long.

122
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:17,633
He had a sharp nose.

123
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:22,467
His eyes,
just average, but fierce.

124
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:26,167
Slim, but...

125
00:07:26,267 --> 00:07:27,900
His face was long.

126
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:32,333
[PENCIL SCRIBBLING]

127
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:39,167
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

128
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:40,633
Like this, sir?

129
00:07:45,367 --> 00:07:46,667
That's the one.

130
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:50,567
Sir, who is he?

131
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:52,867
No one.

132
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,700
We never met.

133
00:07:58,867 --> 00:08:00,433
I didn't avail
of your services.

134
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:02,767
- Do we understand each other?
- Yes, sir.

135
00:08:15,367 --> 00:08:17,200
[JADE] Dad!

136
00:08:17,367 --> 00:08:19,933
<i> Dad, so many kids had fun.</i>

137
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:22,400
<i>Thank you, Dad, for sponsoring
their painting sessions.</i>

138
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:24,033
<i> I'm so happy!</i>

139
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:25,567
<i> That's good to hear.</i>

140
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:27,467
<i>You know anything for you,
my princess.</i>

141
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,367
[CHUCKLES]<i> Thank you, Dad.
</i> You're the best

142
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:32,067
<i> dad in the world!</i> [SMOOCHES]

143
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:36,367
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

144
00:08:36,467 --> 00:08:38,400
[JADE] It's been one month...

145
00:08:38,567 --> 00:08:40,700
<i> since dad died...</i>

146
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:43,033
<i>And you already have
plans to leave us?</i>

147
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:45,633
[FRIDA] Jade, no.
That's not the case.

148
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:47,367
<i> Are you going to leave us?!</i>

149
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,767
Are you going with Uncle Mike?!

150
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:52,100
<i> No, Jade...</i> [INHALES SHARPLY]

151
00:08:52,233 --> 00:08:55,800
<i> - This has nothing--
</i>- I know about the affair, Mom!

152
00:08:55,967 --> 00:09:00,833
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

153
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:04,733
[GRUNTS]

154
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:08,600
[FRIDA]<i> Your uncle and I
</i> are not having an affair.

155
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:13,600
[JADE CRYING] I saw you!

156
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:17,067
<i>I saw you when I was a kid!
I saw you!</i>

157
00:09:17,167 --> 00:09:20,333
<i>Why don't you just
tell the truth?</i>

158
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,900
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

159
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:31,067
[OMINOUS TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

160
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:41,100
[FRIDA SIGHS]

161
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,667
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

162
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:06,267
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

163
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:10,133
Mom had nothing to do with
Uncle Michael and Dad's deaths.

164
00:10:11,033 --> 00:10:12,867
That is what I choose
to believe.

165
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:15,833
I don't want our mother
to go to jail, Jade.

166
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:21,233
And do you think...

167
00:10:21,367 --> 00:10:23,500
that I want that to happen?

168
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:25,300
Do you really think

169
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:27,300
I want mom to go to jail?

170
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:30,567
I don't know, Jade.

171
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:32,800
I don't know what you want.

172
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:35,300
I want the truth, Luna.

173
00:10:35,433 --> 00:10:37,067
[LUNA] The truth?

174
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:40,400
The truth is,
Uncle Michael killed our dad.

175
00:10:40,533 --> 00:10:42,200
What was the reason?

176
00:10:42,367 --> 00:10:44,667
Nobody knows why!

177
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:46,000
Do you want me to bring
them back to life

178
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,267
so they can answer
your question?

179
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:49,433
Luna, you know
what I'm talking about.

180
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:53,067
So, even if mom explained it,

181
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,533
you still think she's the reason
why they killed each other,

182
00:10:55,700 --> 00:10:57,000
is that it, Jade?

183
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:01,167
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:02,500
Okay.

185
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:06,500
Why did the police
go here earlier?

186
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:09,733
Luna, I know where
you're getting at.

187
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,467
Just say it.

188
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:16,033
Did you report it
to the police?

189
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:19,200
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

190
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:20,867
Not to the police, Luna.

191
00:11:22,267 --> 00:11:24,233
I told it to Kiko.

192
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:28,100
I told him that it was
Mom's earring, not yours.

193
00:11:31,067 --> 00:11:32,700
Why did you do that?

194
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,867
Because I'm tired
of all the lies, Luna!

195
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,533
Because you don't want to
believe the truth.

196
00:11:38,633 --> 00:11:41,367
The truth? You also lied!

197
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:44,300
You told them the earring
was yours, even if it wasn't!

198
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:47,733
I'm just trying to
protect our family, Jade.

199
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:51,633
You have nothing to hide if Mom
isn't doing anything wrong.

200
00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:53,067
Fine!

201
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,500
Let's assume what
you're saying is true.

202
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:57,067
Dad's already dead, Jade.

203
00:11:57,167 --> 00:11:59,900
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

204
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:02,233
Can't you forgive our mother?

205
00:12:04,967 --> 00:12:06,167
Don't tell me you're planning
to accuse her

206
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,100
of something even
worse than that?

207
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,500
I don't know, Luna.

208
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:15,767
Then, tell me!

209
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:18,100
Tell me, what do I have to do
to get you to stop?

210
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:21,433
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC
CONTINUES, SWELLS]

211
00:12:21,567 --> 00:12:23,033
Nothing.

212
00:12:23,167 --> 00:12:24,333
Jade...

213
00:12:26,667 --> 00:12:28,500
But maybe I am the problem.

214
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,933
I can't keep my mouth shut.

215
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:36,433
That's why I'll find
the solution.

216
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,600
[JADE SIGHS SHARPLY]

217
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:50,533
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:02,500
[PHONE DINGS]

219
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:11,667
[WATER DRIPPING]

220
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:12,800
What are you doing?

221
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:19,667
Just ask someone
to fix that tomorrow.

222
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:24,167
And just let it drip all night?

223
00:13:27,267 --> 00:13:28,400
Can you hand me the wrench?

224
00:13:33,567 --> 00:13:34,700
The wrench, Justin.

225
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:38,767
[LEON GRUNTS]

226
00:13:41,367 --> 00:13:42,333
[THUDS]

227
00:13:56,567 --> 00:14:02,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

228
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,300
[LEON GRUNTS]

229
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:15,400
This is what we should be doing.

230
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:18,567
Working together.

231
00:14:19,567 --> 00:14:21,300
We're the only men left here.

232
00:14:23,633 --> 00:14:26,300
It's up to us
to protect our family.

233
00:14:28,867 --> 00:14:31,300
This is what Dad wanted too.

234
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,467
That's why...

235
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,833
you should get your life
together, Justin.

236
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:46,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

237
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:59,833
[CHESCA] Dude, what if I
feature your father's death

238
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:01,600
in my vlog?

239
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:03,533
It would make good content!

240
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,767
Now you want to use
my father?

241
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:10,400
Who knows? I might be
able to help you.

242
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:13,967
I mean, I might uncover
something you didn't know.

243
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:15,833
Stop with the nonsense,
will you?

244
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:20,300
- Come on, dude!
- Knock it off, Cheska.

245
00:15:20,300 --> 00:15:22,333
What? Are you going to do it
here in the hotel?

246
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:24,633
Then that'll scare off
our guests.

247
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:28,867
But the murders didn't
happen here, did it?

248
00:15:29,467 --> 00:15:32,267
I'll go to the crime scene.

249
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:35,667
- You have a point.
- See?

250
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:37,600
My idea's great.

251
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:40,733
Now give me some money
so I can get started.

252
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:44,533
Well, your channel doesn't
have any viewers,

253
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:45,967
so go for it.

254
00:15:47,933 --> 00:15:49,667
You meanie.

255
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,867
- [CLEARS THROAT]
- [PHONE CHIMES]

256
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:57,333
[JADE] Let's meet up later.
Don't tell anyone.

257
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,533
What? Who was it?

258
00:16:00,533 --> 00:16:02,300
Nothing. Just a spam text.

259
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:05,367
Yeah, right.

260
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:08,833
I know you're lying.
Your nostrils are flaring.

261
00:16:09,933 --> 00:16:12,233
- Who was it?
- I said it's nothing.

262
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:14,700
"Spam."

263
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:17,867
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,467
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:16:29,467 --> 00:16:31,200
Luna?

266
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,733
Is that you?

267
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:42,733
Who is that?

268
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:49,700
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

269
00:17:02,433 --> 00:17:08,133
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

270
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:09,967
Roy.

271
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:14,267
What are you doing there?

272
00:17:14,267 --> 00:17:21,233
[EERIE MUSIC CONTINUES]

273
00:17:21,267 --> 00:17:23,267
Ma'am, I thought
you were inside.

274
00:17:24,867 --> 00:17:26,067
Uh...

275
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,767
I'm just going to give
this to you because

276
00:17:28,767 --> 00:17:30,067
the maid said...

277
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,767
you didn't want to eat.

278
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,767
Old people say that...

279
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:39,533
bananas help...

280
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:41,967
relax the body.
It'll help you sleep better.

281
00:17:43,267 --> 00:17:46,300
I thought about
what happened earlier...

282
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,133
I thought you might need it.

283
00:17:50,067 --> 00:17:53,800
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,600
Alright. Thank you, Roy.

285
00:18:00,033 --> 00:18:01,667
You can go home now.

286
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:06,867
All right, ma'am.

287
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:13,800
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

288
00:18:15,867 --> 00:18:22,833
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

289
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,233
[SIGHS]

290
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:38,600
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

291
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,033
Is she joking with me?

292
00:18:43,933 --> 00:18:46,200
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

293
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:51,100
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- Hey!

294
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:53,200
- Shh! Shh!
- [MUFFLED SPEAKING]

295
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:01,900
I need to know everything
about Uncle Mike.

296
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:05,300
Why do you look like that?

297
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:07,800
I don't want anyone
to see us.

298
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,933
Do you really think
you won't be recognized?

299
00:19:09,933 --> 00:19:11,867
You're wearing shades at night.

300
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:18,267
Will we talk, or will you keep
talking about my clothes.

301
00:19:18,267 --> 00:19:20,267
Fine. We'll talk.

302
00:19:20,267 --> 00:19:22,200
But first of all,

303
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,733
I just want to tell
you that--

304
00:19:23,733 --> 00:19:24,767
That what?

305
00:19:24,767 --> 00:19:28,200
That you told your siblings
about the earring?

306
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,167
And they called the police,
is that it?

307
00:19:31,233 --> 00:19:33,833
How did you know that?

308
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:35,900
If I were you, I would do
the same.

309
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,400
Hmm. You're not mad?

310
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:43,800
I'm not angry.

311
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:46,067
But I wasn't happy either.

312
00:19:46,067 --> 00:19:48,067
I understand you.

313
00:19:48,067 --> 00:19:51,300
But that doesn't mean
what you did was right.

314
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:54,300
We're still talking
about my family.

315
00:19:55,767 --> 00:19:56,967
Sorry.

316
00:19:56,967 --> 00:20:00,933
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:02,100
That's okay.

318
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:05,900
Just make it up to me.

319
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:09,000
How?

320
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:13,100
I'm sure you've been wondering
why Uncle Mike and my dad

321
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:16,100
killed each other,
because I'm wondering too.

322
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:19,933
That's why you'll help me
find out the truth.

323
00:20:19,933 --> 00:20:22,933
Well, that's
exactly what I want.

324
00:20:22,933 --> 00:20:25,167
- But, i don't--
- Do you remember

325
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:27,300
when I told the you
it was my mom's earring?

326
00:20:28,767 --> 00:20:31,000
Mom said she and Dad
had a fight

327
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,000
before Uncle Mike picked her up.

328
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,800
That's when
she left the earring.

329
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,933
Your parents were fighting? Why?

330
00:20:37,967 --> 00:20:40,500
My dad accused her of having an
affair with your dad.

331
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,167
What?!

332
00:20:42,167 --> 00:20:43,333
You're so loud!

333
00:20:43,333 --> 00:20:48,367
[CURIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

334
00:20:48,367 --> 00:20:50,333
And you believe that?

335
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:52,867
[SIGHS] I don't know, Kiko.

336
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:55,033
I don't know! That's why
I need your help

337
00:20:55,033 --> 00:20:57,800
because I'm going crazy
thinking about it!

338
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,233
What?

339
00:20:59,233 --> 00:21:01,300
Will you help me or not?

340
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:08,200
[CURIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

341
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:14,700
There are three of us siblings,
but we have different mothers.

342
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:17,133
But with Papa,
you can't really deny that--

343
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:18,467
He's a womanizer?

344
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:20,033
No, he's...

345
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,567
Uhm...

346
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:23,533
He has a big...

347
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:24,700
...heart.

348
00:21:25,167 --> 00:21:28,700
That's why he has so much love
to give to different women.

349
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:31,167
Okay.

350
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:39,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:21:44,067 --> 00:21:45,500
Looks like there's
no one here anymore.

352
00:21:45,933 --> 00:21:49,033
You know, Papa isn't here either
to defend himself.

353
00:21:49,133 --> 00:21:50,667
So you believe it now?

354
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:53,400
That our parents had an affair?

355
00:21:53,533 --> 00:21:54,933
Not really.

356
00:21:56,267 --> 00:21:57,733
Then what did I see?

357
00:21:57,900 --> 00:21:59,933
So that was nothing?
I just imagined it?

358
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:02,733
Okay fine, let's say
we did find something out.

359
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:05,533
And let's assume that what
you're saying is actually true.

360
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:07,533
But Jade, what does that change?

361
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:09,567
What does that have to do
with Papa's death?

362
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,900
I don't know, Kiko.

363
00:22:13,467 --> 00:22:17,067
Don't tell me
you're thinking your mother

364
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:20,100
killed your father so she and
my father could be together?

365
00:22:20,933 --> 00:22:21,800
So that...

366
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:23,633
they could finally be free
to love each other,

367
00:22:23,767 --> 00:22:26,767
but then something went wrong,
so Papa got involved?

368
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:30,100
- Kiko...
- Are you serious?!

369
00:22:30,233 --> 00:22:32,700
I don't know, Kiko!
I really don't know!

370
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:36,200
That's why I need your help
to find out the truth!

371
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:38,267
So right now, tell me,
yes or no?

372
00:22:38,433 --> 00:22:39,733
Will you help me?

373
00:22:39,833 --> 00:22:46,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

374
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:54,967
<i>If they find out about this,
they're going to get mad.</i>

375
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:57,567
<i>We're talking about
my mother here, okay?</i>

376
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,667
<i>And we're investigating
my father too.</i>

377
00:22:59,833 --> 00:23:00,800
<i> So just make a promise.</i>

378
00:23:00,967 --> 00:23:02,933
<i>- We'll make a dance trend.
- Hey, Jade!</i>

379
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:04,500
<i>- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?</i>

380
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:05,733
<i> I'm fine, I'm fine.</i>

381
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:08,000
<i>Almost everything here
on the island belongs to us.</i>

382
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:09,500
<i> Except for the Hotel 88.</i>

383
00:23:09,667 --> 00:23:10,633
<i> Edward!</i>

384
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:12,267
<i>This is the sea!
There are no rules here!</i>

385
00:23:12,367 --> 00:23:13,467
<i> Let's hold the meeting here.</i>

386
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:16,300
<i>I am Justin Almazan
at your service.</i>

387
00:23:16,433 --> 00:23:17,300
<i> Oh, whatever.</i>

388
00:23:17,467 --> 00:23:19,067
In three days, Sari will resign.

389
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:21,300
<i>How did they find out
that you were here?</i>

390
00:23:21,433 --> 00:23:22,667
<i> What are you hiding?</i>

391
00:23:22,867 --> 00:23:24,167
<i>Are you really that scared
that the truth might come out?</i>

392
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:26,700
<i>If there really is a folder,
then where would it go?</i>

393
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:28,800
<i>The four of us
should stay united.</i>

394
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:30,467
<i> We can't fall apart.</i>

395
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:31,667
<i>But there are only three
of us now.</i>

396
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:33,033
<i> So where is Jade?</i>

